# ğŸ bug report

### Affected Package
I'm using Angular 7 but I'm sure it goes beyond that. I've posted this on the VSCode page and they directed me here.


### Description

I am using the latest version of VSCode 1.35.0 and Angular 7. I came across an odd bug. I'm pretty sure it's a bug and not a config setting.

In angular, my component folder has 3 items in it, my .html, .scss, and .ts files. When I create functions in the component ts such as:

```
public ThisIsAFunction() { }
public ThisIsAnother_Function() { }
```
Now in the html file I will create an element and try to assign a property like so:

```<button (click)="this.ThisIsAFunction()">DoFunction</button>```

The issue here is, when I start typing "this.ThisIsA" the intellisense will only display "ThisIsAFunction" in the list of available functions. Any functions named with an underscore will never show up.


## ğŸ”¬ Minimal Reproduction
<!--
Any VSCode + Angular project. Create function with _ in ts and try to assign it in the html.
--> 


